-- Coal of Africa Drops Most in Three Weeks After Announcing Share Placement
-- Janice Kew
-- 2010-06-17T07:19:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/coal-of-africa-drops-most-in-three-weeks-after-announcing-share-placement.html

          
          
             Coal of Africa Ltd. fell the most in
three weeks in Johannesburg trading after the coal producer
raised about 55 million pounds ($81 million) selling shares.  
 The stock declined as much as 55 cents, or 4.4 percent, to
12.10 rand, the biggest intraday drop since May 25, and traded
at 12.20 rand as of 9:16 a.m. local time.  
          
          


  


        